# Ashveil — Project Rules

## Spec
Read `docs/ASHVEIL_SPEC.md` for full architecture, design system, data model, AI pipeline, and build phases.

## What This Is
Mobile-first multiplayer AI-powered tabletop RPG. 2-6 players, shared state, AI or Human DM, turn-based, real-time via Pusher.

## Stack
Next.js 15+ (App Router), TypeScript (strict), Tailwind v4, Framer Motion, Zustand, Neon Postgres + Drizzle, Upstash Redis, Pusher, NextAuth, fal.ai, Vercel.

## Non-Negotiable Rules
1. Canonical DB state is truth — AI never directly mutates it
2. Every AI output validated with Zod before use
3. Turn order enforced server-side with Redis locks
4. Narration 60-140 words, structured JSON output
5. Images async, never block gameplay
6. Mobile-first — thumb zone, no clutter

## Delegation (CRITICAL for cost)
- ALWAYS use Task tool with `model: "fast"` for: scaffolding, boilerplate, repetitive code, file creation, simple components, tests, migrations
- Reserve Opus (yourself) for: architectural decisions, reviewing fast agent output, complex AI orchestration logic, debugging
- Do NOT write large code blocks directly — delegate to fast agents with detailed instructions, then review
- Do NOT create markdown docs, READMEs, or documentation files unless explicitly asked
- Keep responses concise — no verbose explanations unless asked

